{
  "version": 2,
  "html": "<article class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n\n  \n  <section class=\"gradient-slate-dark text-white p-5 md:p-10 rounded-2xl mb-8\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white\">The Real Question Nobody's Asking</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-200 leading-relaxed\">\n      Your family's been dealing with 12-hour apagones. You've got money set aside. Now you're staring at Amazon wondering: do I send solar panels that need installation, or a power station they can just plug in? Here's the thing—both solve the problem, but they solve <em>different</em> problems. And if you pick wrong, you've just shipped 50 pounds of expensive disappointment.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-10\">\n    <p>\n      Let's cut through the marketing noise. <strong>Solar panel kits</strong> are permanent installations—they go on the roof, wire into batteries, and generate power as long as the sun shines. They're the long game. <strong>Power stations</strong> are essentially giant battery packs you charge beforehand (from the grid, a car, or yes, solar panels) and use during blackouts. They're the quick fix.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      For Cuba specifically, you're weighing a few realities: Who's going to install panels on an aging concrete roof? Does your family have somewhere secure to mount them? Can they handle basic electrical work, or do they need something that just... works? And critically—how long are these apagones lasting now? Because an 8-hour blackout needs a different solution than rolling 4-hour cuts.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      The shipping math matters too. Panel kits are heavy and fragile. Power stations are dense but compact. Both hit customs scrutiny, but panels sometimes raise more eyebrows because they're clearly \"infrastructure.\" I've seen kits sail through and I've seen them held for weeks. Power stations tend to clear faster—they look like oversized phone chargers to inspectors who don't know better.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"bg-sunglow/10 border-2 border-sunglow p-5 md:p-8 rounded-xl mb-10\">\n    <h3 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3\">The Quick Answer</h3>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-lg\">\n      For most families dealing with unpredictable Cuban grid situations, <strong>a complete solar kit with charge controller</strong> wins long-term. The Renogy 400W kit stands out with a perfect 5★ rating and everything needed for installation. But if your family needs power <em>tomorrow</em> without any setup? A portable station or plug-and-play system gets them through tonight's apagón.\n    </p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FG2VF2V2?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-5 inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n      See the Renogy 400W Kit →\n    </a>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">Complete Solar Kits: The Long-Term Play</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8\">These come with panels, charge controllers, and mounting hardware. Your family (or a local electrician) handles installation, but once it's up, it's generating free power for years.</p>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl mb-8 ring-2 ring-lime ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Editor's Pick</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/716Cn4QfDsL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy Premium 400W Solar Kit - complete system with MPPT controller\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0FG2VF2V2\" class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Renogy Premium 400W 12V Solar Kit</h3>\n          <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">5★ (505 reviews)</span>\n          <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          <p class=\"mt-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n            <strong>VERDICT: The one reviewers actually rave about.</strong>\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"mt-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400\">\n            Perfect 5-star rating isn't an accident. This kit includes the 40A MPPT controller (more efficient than PWM), Bluetooth monitoring, Z-brackets, and proper tray cables. The \"New Version\" designation means Renogy addressed earlier complaints. Four 100W panels give flexibility—mount them separately if roof space is awkward. Reviewers consistently mention the instructions are actually followable, which matters when you're explaining installation over WhatsApp.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FG2VF2V2?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-5 inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n            Check Price on Amazon →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-6\">\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n        <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81NGDGKhAJL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 400W Premium Solar Kit with Bluetooth module\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0BPY72B9R\" class=\"text-lg md:text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">ECO-WORTHY 400W Premium Solar Kit</h3>\n          <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.3★ (435 reviews)</span>\n          <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n            <strong>VERDICT: Solid alternative, slightly lower ratings.</strong>\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"mt-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400\">\n            Same 400W output, same MPPT controller, same Bluetooth monitoring. So why the lower rating? Reviewers mention occasional shipping damage and less detailed instructions. The panels themselves perform well—it's the unboxing experience that costs it stars. If it arrives intact, you're golden.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BPY72B9R?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-800 dark:text-white font-medium no-underline hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 transition-colors text-sm\">\n            View on Amazon →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-6\">\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n        <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Ps3BsTkML._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 200W Solar Panel Kit for beginners\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B09RZZHHHM\" class=\"text-lg md:text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">ECO-WORTHY 200W 12V/24V Starter Kit</h3>\n          <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.6★ (465 reviews)</span>\n          <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n            <strong>VERDICT: Best entry point if 400W feels like overkill.</strong>\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"mt-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400\">\n            200 watts won't run an air conditioner, but it'll keep phones charged, lights on, and a fan spinning through the night. The 30A PWM controller is simpler tech than MPPT but perfectly adequate at this scale. Higher rating than the 400W ECO-WORTHY because smaller shipments arrive less damaged. Smart first step before committing to a bigger system.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09RZZHHHM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-800 dark:text-white font-medium no-underline hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 transition-colors text-sm\">\n            View on Amazon →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <blockquote class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-flame border-l-4 border-flame pl-6 my-10\">\n    \"400 watts sounds like a lot until you realize a small fridge alone needs 100-200W continuously.\"\n  </blockquote>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">High-Wattage Panel Sets: When You Need Serious Power</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8\">These are panels only—no controllers, no mounting hardware. You're buying raw generating capacity for an existing system or building something custom.</p>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8\">\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71pz5YPEjGL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"STAR 870W Solar Panel Set - 2 panels\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0DFBSBWDG\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">STAR 870W (2x 435W)</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.2★</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">\n          Two massive 435W panels for 48V/24V systems. Full-screen design maximizes surface area. Maintenance-free but <strong>heavy</strong>—shipping these intact requires serious packaging.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DFBSBWDG?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-800 dark:text-white font-medium no-underline text-sm hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 transition-colors\">\n            View Details →\n          </a>\n      </div>\n\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg ring-2 ring-sunglow ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n        <span class=\"bg-sunglow text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-3 inline-block\">Best Value</span>\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81sCnup-X5L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Callsun 800W Solar Panel Set - 8 panels\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0FZKR417P\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Callsun 800W (8x 100W)</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">\n          Eight smaller panels = easier shipping, flexible mounting, spare capacity if one breaks. Works with 12V through 60V systems. The smart choice for Cuban rooftops with irregular layouts.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FZKR417P?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-sunglow text-raisin font-medium no-underline text-sm hover:bg-sunglow/80 transition-colors\">\n            View Details →\n          </a>\n      </div>\n\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/713HUQV3X8L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"18BB 800W N-Type Solar Panels - 4 panels\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0FFGTMG46\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">18BB 800W N-Type (4x 200W)</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.3★</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">\n          N-Type cells handle heat better than standard monocrystalline—relevant for Cuban summers. Mid-range pricing at $$$ makes this the budget-conscious high-wattage option. Four 200W panels balance size and output.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FFGTMG46?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-800 dark:text-white font-medium no-underline text-sm hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 transition-colors\">\n            View Details →\n          </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">How Much Solar Do They Actually Need?</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">Blackout length matters more than you think. Use this to size the system right.</p>\n    <solar-sizing>\n  </solar-sizing></section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">Plug-and-Play: Zero Installation Required</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8\">These systems plug directly into a wall outlet. The panels charge batteries during grid hours, then the inverter feeds power back when the grid dies. Sounds like magic. Here's the catch.</p>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-6 mb-8\">\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"lg:col-span-3 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/51ZNk5gm2ML._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Plug and Play 800W Solar System - wall outlet connection\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B09D61CP1T\" class=\"text-lg md:text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Plug and Play 800W Solar System</h3>\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.5★ (455 reviews)</span>\n            <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n            <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">\n              <strong>VERDICT: Brilliant concept with a Cuban caveat.</strong>\n            </p>\n            <p class=\"mt-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400\">\n              800W panels + 800W inverter, literally plug into any outlet. The system backfeeds into your home wiring. <em>However</em>—this assumes stable grid voltage and proper grounding. Cuban electrical systems can be... creative. Reviewers love the simplicity; just verify the home's wiring can handle it first.\n            </p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09D61CP1T?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-medium no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors text-sm\">\n              Check Price →\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      \n      <div class=\"lg:col-span-2 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81audnUHPBL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH Complete Solar System\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-44 object-contain bg-slate-50 mb-4\" />\n        <h3 data-asin=\"B0BQV4YG1T\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH System</h3>\n        <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.4★</span>\n        <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n        <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">\n          The nuclear option. 2340W of panels, 5000W inverter, 48V system. This runs a small house. Twelve panels, though—shipping is a project unto itself. For families with serious power needs and someone who knows electrical work.\n        </p>\n        <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BQV4YG1T?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-800 dark:text-white font-medium no-underline text-sm hover:bg-slate-300 dark:hover:bg-slate-600 transition-colors\">\n            View Details →\n          </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">Portable &amp; Foldable: The Flexible Option</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8\">Not everyone has roof access. These fold up, store away, and deploy wherever the sun hits. Perfect for apartments, renters, or families who might move.</p>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"space-y-4\">\n      \n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-4 md:p-5 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-36 md:w-44 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81NIQFQ-ajL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"DOKIO 300W Portable Foldable Solar Panel Kit\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-36 sm:h-40 object-contain bg-slate-50\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B07JPH4PHG\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1\">DOKIO 300W Portable Foldable Kit</h3>\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.2★</span>\n            <span class=\"ml-2 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n            <p class=\"mt-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">\n              Folds to 20x38 inches, weighs 15 lbs. Separate controller included. Charges 12V batteries or pairs with power stations. The dual USB ports are handy for direct device charging. Solid middle ground between permanent and truly portable.\n            </p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07JPH4PHG?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-3 inline-block text-